34
00:02:38.097 --> 00:02:41.524
And Steve Jobs famously
kinda represented this.

35
00:02:41.524 --> 00:02:46.505
I'm sure you've heard of the Steve Jobs'
reality distortion field.

36
00:02:46.505 --> 00:02:50.588
That when Steve Jobs was
around talking about an idea,

37
00:02:50.588 --> 00:02:56.103
it suddenly is all seemed to make sense
and it all seemed to be a great idea.

38
00:02:56.103 --> 00:03:01.834
And when he left the room, suddenly, you
realized it wasn't such a great idea and

39
00:03:01.834 --> 00:03:05.260
actually it's gonna be
really difficult to do.

40
00:03:05.260 --> 00:03:09.095
That is an example of the halo effect, and

41
00:03:09.095 --> 00:03:14.027
the halo effect is effectively
when we as human beings

42
00:03:14.027 --> 00:03:18.752
associate to unrelated
factors with one another.

43
00:03:18.752 --> 00:03:25.842
So the typical example was the charisma
of Steve Jobs carried you along and

44
00:03:25.842 --> 00:03:30.310
convinced you that the idea was good,
right?

45
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:33.339
A more extreme example
of it is that in tests,

46
00:03:33.339 --> 00:03:38.544
it's found that attractive people
are considered a much more trustworthy.

47
00:03:38.544 --> 00:03:42.373
So you're more likely to trust
an attractive person than

48
00:03:42.373 --> 00:03:44.135
a non attractive person.

49
00:03:44.135 --> 00:03:47.258
Which is why you trust every
word from my mouth now.

50
00:03:47.258 --> 00:03:49.706
But that's ridiculous
if you think about it,

51
00:03:49.706 --> 00:03:53.494
because there should be no correlation
between those two whatsoever.

52
00:03:53.494 --> 00:03:58.789
You can be incredibly attractive and
a mass murder, yet, there is something

53
00:03:58.789 --> 00:04:03.447
in our psychology that means we do
associate these kinds of things.

54
00:04:03.447 --> 00:04:07.875
And, of course, the result of that
is we associate, for example,

55
00:04:07.875 --> 00:04:12.788
the attractiveness of a website with
the quality of the product behind it.

56
00:04:12.788 --> 00:04:18.206
If the website looks unprofessional,
if it looks dated or whatever else,

57
00:04:18.206 --> 00:04:23.366
then we might conclude that the product
isn't very loved or cared for.

58
00:04:23.366 --> 00:04:27.988
So the halo effect is an important
effect and does have a knock on value.

59
00:04:27.988 --> 00:04:32.890
And you can see this in a very tangible
and very real way, the power of

60
00:04:32.890 --> 00:04:38.235
aesthetics to actually influence our
buying decisions and our actions.

61
00:04:38.235 --> 00:04:41.140
