we need people to feel in order

92
00:06:41.104 --> 00:06:43.965
to encourage them to act, right?

93
00:06:43.965 --> 00:06:46.744
Do they need to feel
that you're trustworthy?

94
00:06:46.744 --> 00:06:49.139
Do they need to feel friendly towards you?

95
00:06:49.139 --> 00:06:50.952
Do they need to feel positive?

96
00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:53.068
What do they need to feel, or

97
00:06:53.068 --> 00:06:58.279
what do you want them to think about
your brand is another way to put it.

98
00:06:58.279 --> 00:07:03.861
And we ascertain a few words that we all
agree on, that are words that we think or

99
00:07:03.861 --> 00:07:07.752
our users think will resonate
most with the audience,

100
00:07:07.752 --> 00:07:10.810
in order to encourage them to take action.

101
00:07:10.810 --> 00:07:16.982
And then I start designing around those
words exploring different colors,

102
00:07:16.982 --> 00:07:22.297
and typography, and
imagery that I feel represent those words.

103
00:07:22.297 --> 00:07:30.079
And you could do some really cool stuff
with just a little bit of thought, really.

104
00:07:30.079 --> 00:07:31.558
So let's take this example.

105
00:07:31.558 --> 00:07:34.500
This is an example from the smashing
magazine, a membership site.

106
00:07:34.500 --> 00:07:37.266
I don't know whether you're aware of it or
not.

107
00:07:37.266 --> 00:07:41.939
But everything in this is designed
to put you in a good mood,

108
00:07:41.939 --> 00:07:44.096
to make you feel positive.

109
00:07:44.096 --> 00:07:49.415
From the vibrant colors being used
to the smiling cat illustrations,

110
00:07:49.415 --> 00:07:54.747
the fact that all the shapes on
the illustration, curved and gentle.

111
00:07:54.747 --> 00:08:00.995
That the whole feel of it even down to the
text and the way that the text is worded,

112
00:08:00.995 --> 00:08:06.985
and then the little delight or animations
where you roll over them, right?

113
00:08:06.985 --> 00:08:12.503
Everything in that design is to make
you feel positive and why do we care?

114
00:08:12.503 --> 00:08:17.692
Because the more positive we feel,
the lower our cognitive load is,

115
00:08:17.692 --> 00:08:22.344
the more trusting we are,
the more positive we're gonna view

116
00:08:22.344 --> 00:08:26.296
the website because of the halo effect,
et cetera.

117
00:08:26.296 --> 00:08:31.695
So that's a great little bit of using
styling and shapes and animation and

118
00:08:31.695 --> 00:08:37.370
imagery and copy and all those things
together to create a great impression.

119
00:08:37.370 --> 00:08:42.088
And one of the things that I
like in particular about this is

120
00:08:42.088 --> 00:08:45.765
the little animations or rollover, right?

121
00:08:45.765 --> 00:08:49.978
So they're really subtle but
they make you go and actually,

122
00:08:49.978 --> 00:08:53.043
those kinds of own moments so that's nice.

